channel.title: Exception in thread main java.lang.noclassdeffounderror: Gui
channel.description:
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Gui Caused by: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: Gui at java.net.URLClassLoader$1.run(Unknown Source) at java.security.AccessController.doPrivileged(Native Method) at java.net.URLClassLoader.findClass(Unknown Source) at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) at sun.misc.Launcher$AppClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) Could not find the main class: Gui. Program will exit. Press any key to continue . . .
Anyone have any idea as to how to solve?
TeamViewer would be nice :)

item.title: Exception in thread main java.lang.noclassdeffounderror: Gui
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“xxInfamousxx, post:3, topic:478854”]I searched where the file is looking: C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre6\bin\java.exe

Should I edit the run file, and change its path to the location of the GUI?[/quote]
Yes. You need to make sure it’s finding Gui.class, looking for Gui.java would do nothing.
